<item>
            <title>[LU-16656] Improve location of &apos;out:&apos; in ll_file_io_generic</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16656</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The location of the &apos;out:&apos; label in ll_file_io_generic is a bit scary, because it skips part of the setup for io_restart, where partial io is taken in to account.&#160; This is safe today because &apos;out:&apos; is only used before calls to cl_io_loop, so a partial IO is impossible, but if &apos;out;&apos; is ever used later in the function, it will be incorrect.&#160; Let&apos;s move it now rather than leave a trap for the unwary.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
